                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10370",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jayson",
                        "name": "jayson",
                        "displayName": "Jayson Minard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Consider by 0.3.0 and either reject or accept and build the feature.  Decision needs to be made.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jayson",
                        "name": "jayson",
                        "displayName": "Jayson Minard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-09T00:48:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-09T00:48:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10388",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mislav",
                        "name": "mislav",
                        "displayName": "Mislav Marohni?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Decision is going to be made. Right now I'm pondering about what happens at 13:09 and whether it's right or wrong. Is the possibility to \"intervalize\" lifetime going to solve problems caused by not having a system to invalidate cache records?\n\nFor now, you should really invalidate records by tags manually when you change things. For instance, your administrative interface should invalidate all 'thumbnail' records when changing thumbnail details.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mislav",
                        "name": "mislav",
                        "displayName": "Mislav Marohni?",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-09T08:02:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-09T08:02:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10398",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fabicz",
                        "name": "fabicz",
                        "displayName": "Marek Nos",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": ">For now, you should really invalidate records by tags manually when you change things.\n\nAs stated in \"12:50) AdminA makes changes to data but there isn't real connection to the cache so cache can't be deleted. E.g. changes in photo title doesn't reflects to article's cache.\". There're different records in different tables. It should be much more complex e.g. it should be set of articles from given section. And order of these article should be dependent on priorities which _changes in time_. \n\nAnd it means cacheB as list of 3 articles in right column of PageB and cacheA as list of 10 articles in middle column of PageA should be the same. And it's possible with intervalize lifetime even the priorities changes in time because caches are invalidated at the same time.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fabicz",
                        "name": "fabicz",
                        "displayName": "Marek Nos",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-09T14:55:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-09T14:55:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11344",
                    "author": {
